The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, October 29, 2003 				 Husband and in-laws held
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Krishnagar, Oct. 28: In-laws of a housewife were arrested here last night after she allegedly committed suicide. 																								Srabanti Daw, 21, a mother of two children  one a two-year-old and the 10 months  was married to Tapan, a PCO operator, three years ago. Neighbours found her charred yesterday. Her father Dependu Biswas alleged that Tapan used to torture her demanding more dowry. The husband, his father Puridas  and mother Swarnomoyi were charged with provoking the daughter-in-law  to commit suicide. The trio was picked up minutes after  Srabanti died in Saktinagar State General Hospital.
